The paper deals with the problem of constructing and evaluating behavioural hypotheses in multiagent systems, which is a core topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of statistical methods for hypothesis testing, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper's focus on multiagent systems and interaction processes suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of multiagent systems (cs.MA) and control systems (cs.SY).
